Preferences:



MasTec prefers, but does not require, that candidates have experience in the local area;
Certifications in Project or Program Management and experience utilizing this approach to project execution.

Requirements:



Bachelor's Degree in Construction Management or related Engineering discipline preferred or equivalent combination of experience and education:
15 years of relevant supervisory and leadership experience on complex major telecommunications projects:
Strong working knowledge of site analysis, permitting and approvals, budget control, estimating, project scheduling and construction coordination;
Excellent ability to communicate orally and in writing;
Excellent customer and Client service skills;
Strong capabilities in analysis and problem solving;
Must to enthusiastic and driven to excellence;
A strong team builder with the ability to motivate others to strive for and exceed project obligations and expectations;
Demonstrated ability to manage staff and a strong understanding of the entire corporate utility infrastructure functions from planning to delivery;
Understanding drawings, permits and specifications relevant to the fiber, cellular, and/or cable industry;
Computer literate, knowledge of Windows and Microsoft Office (Word, Excel and Power point) and Adobe.

Essential Duties and Responsibilities:



Project walkouts to ensure design is feasible and efficient;

Project research for projects to include:



Develop site plan and images;
List of site assets;
Define labor and materials for project;
Permitting needs;
Infrastructure and Node or plant connection points;
Locate service needed;
City, County and State requirements or restrictions;
Development of work packet to include project detail, maps, images and supporting files for review by other functional project team members;
Network and asset knowledge and planning to include aerial and underground project labor and materials as defined by the Client;
Responsible for ensuring company standard safety practices;
Safety violation enforcement and disciplinary action reviews;
Will take the lead in Safety training and compliance;
Provides specialized technical expertise in support of the Quality program, including specialized inspection and testing techniques, quality training, statistical methods, audits, quality tools for problem solving and assessment;
Implements principles of performance evaluation in collaboration with the PMO and the Client;
Full responsibility for collection of data deliverables from the field to the Client.
